discussion.p:
 made optional fully constexpr, but missed its cousin
semiregular-box (which was renamed to copyable-box by 
). Most operations of copyable-box are already 
constexpr simply because copyable-box is specified in terms of optional;
the only missing ones are the assignment operators layered on top when the wrapped type
isn't assignable itself.

blockquote.pre:
constexpr copyable-box& operator=(const copyable-box& that)
  noexcept(is_nothrow_copy_constructible_v<T>) {
  if (this != addressof(that)) {
    if (that) emplace(*that);
    else reset();
  }
  return *this;
}

constexpr copyable-box& operator=(copyable-box&& that)
  noexcept(is_nothrow_move_constructible_v<T>) {
  if (this != addressof(that)) {
    if (that) emplace(std::move(*that));
    else reset();
  }
  return *this;
}
